<chapter xml:id="getting-started" xreflabel="Getting Started" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
    xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="5.1">
    <title>Getting Started</title>
    <para>The best way to get started using &productshort; is to make yourself familiar with the
        menus and interface. This will give you an understanding of what features and functions are
        available and how to find them when using the program. Once familiar, it is recomended that
        you adjust the basic settings available in the <guilabel>Preferences</guilabel>.</para>
    <para condition="desktop">This chapter is about getting you aquainted with &productdesktop;
        edition. It gives you a quick tour of the Main Workspace of &productshort; including the
        Main Menu and View Panels. It also covers setting of the preferences so that you may
        configure &productshort; to work with the setting options of your choice.</para>
    <sect1 condition="desktop" xml:id="desktop-main-workspace" xreflabel="Main Workspace">
        <title>Main Workspace</title>
        <para>The &productshort; workspace is comprised of a <xref xlink:href="#main-menu"/> and
                <xref xlink:href="#view-panels"/>.</para>
        <sect2 xml:id="main-menu" xreflabel="Main Menu">
            <title>Main Menu</title>
            <para>Each menu on the Main Menu displays a list of menu items. Menus may be accessed
                using a mouse pointer or accelerator keys.</para>
            <variablelist>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term><guimenu>File</guimenu> (<keycombo>
                            <keycap>Alt</keycap>
                            <keycap>F</keycap>
                        </keycombo>)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>New logbook</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>N</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Starts a new empty logbook. </para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Open Logbook</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>O</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the <guilabel>Open file</guilabel> dialog that
                                        lists previously saved logbook files and enables opening of
                                        a selected logbook file.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Save</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>S</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Saves the current open logbook.</para>
                                    <para>When a logbook has never been saved, this behaves like a
                                            <guimenuitem>Save as</guimenuitem> operation.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Save as</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>V</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the Save as dialog that enables saving of the
                                        current open logbook to a new logbook file.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Open cloud storage</guimenuitem></term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Connects to the &productcloud;, fetches data and displays
                                        divelogs.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Save to cloud storage</guimenuitem></term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Connects to the &productcloud;, sends data changes to the
                                        cloud storage.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Cloud storage online</guimenuitem></term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Toggles saving of the current logbook between local cache
                                        and cloud storage.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Close</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>W</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Closes the current open logbook without exiting
                                        &productshort;</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Export</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>E</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the <guilabel>Export dive log files</guilabel>
                                        dialog that can be used to export &productshort; logfile
                                        format to file formats used by other divelog programs,
                                        exchange formats and presentation formats.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Print</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>P</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the <guilabel>Print</guilabel> dialog that can be
                                        used to define print layout options, preview results and
                                        send data to a printer.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Preferences</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>,</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the <guilabel>Preferences</guilabel> dialog that
                                        can be used to set user preferences related to various
                                        functional areas of the software.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Find moved media files</guimenuitem></term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para/>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Configure dive computer</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap/>
                                        <keycap>Shift</keycap>
                                        <keycap>C</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the <guilabel>Configure dive computer</guilabel>
                                        dialog that can be used to define communication and settings
                                        properties for various dive computer types.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Recent Logbooks</guimenuitem></term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Lists four of the most recent logbooks to be opened in
                                        order most to least recent.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Quit</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>Q</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Terminates &productshort;.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term><guimenu>Edit</guimenu> (<keycombo>
                            <keycap>Alt</keycap>
                            <keycap>E</keycap>
                        </keycombo>)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Undo</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>Z</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Reverts the most recent changes made to an unsaved logbook
                                        from most to least recent.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Redo</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>Shift</keycap>
                                        <keycap>Z</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Roles back most recent changes undone by an
                                            <guimenuitem>Undo</guimenuitem> operation to an unsaved
                                        logbook from most to least recent.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term><guimenu>Import</guimenu> (<keycombo>
                            <keycap>Alt</keycap>
                            <keycap>I</keycap>
                        </keycombo>)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Import from dive computer</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>D</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the <guilabel>Download from dive
                                            computer</guilabel> dialog that enables selection of
                                        specific dive computer to download from and setting of
                                        download options.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Import from log files</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>I</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the <guilabel>Open dive log file</guilabel>
                                        dialog that enables listing and selection of log files
                                        stored in the <application>DataTrak</application> file
                                        format.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Import from divelogs.de</guimenuitem></term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the <guilabel>Web service connection</guilabel>
                                        dialog that enables definition of divelog.de authentication
                                        details and starting of an operation to fetch divelogs from
                                        divelog.de.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term><guimenu>Log</guimenu> (<keycombo>
                            <keycap>Alt</keycap>
                            <keycap>L</keycap>
                        </keycombo>)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Add dive</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>+</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para/>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Plan dive</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>L</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the &productplanner; module that enables dive
                                        planning.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Edit dive in planner</guimenuitem></term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Opens a dive plan selected in the <guilabel>Dive
                                            List</guilabel> in the &productplanner; for
                                        editing.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Copy dive components</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>C</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the <guilabel>Components selection</guilabel>
                                        dialog that enables copy of select properties of a divelog
                                        to memory from which it can be pasted into another
                                        divelog.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Paste dive components</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>V</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Pastes previously copied dive components into the divelog
                                        currently selected in the <guilabel>Dive
                                        List</guilabel>.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Renumber</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>R</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the <guilabel>Renumber</guilabel> dialog that
                                        enables renumbering of all dives starting from a given
                                        number.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Auto group</guimenuitem></term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Groups records in the &paneldivelist; by location.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Edit device names</guimenuitem></term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the <guilabel>Edit dive computer
                                            nicknames</guilabel> dialog that enables removing dive
                                        computers from a list and appending nicknames to dive
                                        computers.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem/> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>F</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the <guilabel>Filter</guilabel> sub panel that
                                        enables the &paneldivelist; to be filtered based on Tag,
                                        Person, Location and Suits properties.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term><guimenu>View</guimenu> (<keycombo>
                            <keycap>Alt</keycap>
                            <keycap>V</keycap>
                        </keycombo>)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guilabel/> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>1</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays all <xref xlink:href="#view-panels"/> in the Main
                                        Workspace.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guilabel/> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>1</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para/>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term>&paneldivelist; (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>2</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays on the &paneldivelist; view panel in the Main
                                        Workspace.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guilabel>Profile</guilabel> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>3</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays on the &paneldiveprofile;view panel in the Main
                                        Workspace.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guilabel>Profile</guilabel> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>4</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays on the &paneldiveprofile;view panel in the Main
                                        Workspace.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guilabel>Map</guilabel> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>5</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays on the &paneldivemap;view panel in the Main
                                        Workspace.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guilabel>Yearly Statistics</guilabel> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>Y</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the <guilabel>Yearly Statistics</guilabel> report
                                        window.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guilabel>Previous dive computer</guilabel> (
                                        <keycap>Left</keycap> )</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>???</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guilabel>Next dive computer</guilabel> (
                                        <keycap>Right</keycap> )</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para/>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term><guimenu>Share on</guimenu></term>
                    <listitem>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term>Facebook</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Share the current selected or open dive on
                                        Facebook.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term>Connect to</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays a sub-menu listing social media sites. When an
                                        item is selected displays a configuration dialog that
                                        enables setup and authentication with the selected social
                                        media service.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term><guimenu>Help</guimenu> (<keycombo>
                            <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                            <keycap>H</keycap>
                        </keycombo>)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guilabel>About Subsurface</guilabel></term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the <guilabel>About Subsurface</guilabel> dialog
                                        that displays the software version and provides quick access
                                        to the License, Credits and Website.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guilabel>Check for updates</guilabel></term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Checks for newer versions of &productshort;</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guilabel>User survey</guilabel></term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the <guilabel>User survey</guilabel>
                                        dialog.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guilabel>User Manual</guilabel> ( <keycap>F1</keycap>
                                    )</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the &productshort; User Manual.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
            </variablelist>
        </sect2>
        <sect2 xml:id="view-panels" xreflabel="View Panels">
            <title>View Panels</title>
            <para>The dividers between panels can be dragged to change the size of any of the
                panels. &productshort; remembers the position of the dividers, so the next time
                starts it uses the positions of the dividers from the last time the program was
                used.</para>

            <para>If a single dive is selected in the *Dive List*, the dive location, detailed
                information and profile of the _selected dive_ are shown in the respective panels.
                If several dives are selected, the last highlighted dive is the _selected dive_, but
                summary data of all _highlighted dives_ is shown in the *Stats* tab of the *Info*
                panel (maximum, minimum and average depths, durations, water temperatures and SAC;
                total time and number of dives selected).</para>
            <variablelist>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>&paneldivelist; (bottom left)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Shows the dives in the user's dive log. Dives in the list can be
                            selected by clicking on a record. The selected record is highlighted. In
                            adding to selection by mouse click, the <keycap>UP</keycap> and
                                <keycap>DOWN</keycap> keys on the keyboard can also be used to
                            change selection. Multiple dive records can be selected by holding down
                            the <keycap>CTRL</keycap> key and clicking additional records.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>&paneldivemap;(bottom right)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Shows the dive site location of the record selected in the
                            &paneldivelist;. The dive location is displayed centered on a world map
                            and marked by a dive flag. The map scale can be increased or
                            decreased.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>&paneldiveinfo;(top left)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Shows more detailed information on the dive selected in the
                            &paneldivelist;, including some statistics for the selected dive or for
                            all highlighted dive(s).</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>&paneldiveprofile;(top right)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Shows a graphical dive profile of the selected dive in the
                            &paneldivelist;. You can zoom into the dive profile for a more detailed
                            view.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
            </variablelist>
        </sect2>
    </sect1>
