    <sect1 xml:id="setting-preferences" xreflabel="Setting Preferences">
        <title>Setting Preferences</title>
        <para condition="desktop">The <guilabel>Preferences</guilabel> dialog enables setting of
            your personal preferences and requirements when working with &productdesktop;. Settings
            saved in the <guilabel>Preferences</guilabel> will remain persistant for all future
            sessions of the program. Settings within the <guilabel>Preferences</guilabel> dialog are
            grouped as follows:</para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para><xref xlink:href="#general-settings"/></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><xref xlink:href="#units-settings"/></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><xref xlink:href="#language-settings"/></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><xref xlink:href="#profile-settings"/></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><xref xlink:href="#georeference-settings"/></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><xref xlink:href="#network-settings"/></para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <para>Select <menuchoice>
                <guimenu>File</guimenu>
                <guimenuitem>Preferences</guimenuitem>
            </menuchoice> to display the <guilabel>Preferences</guilabel> dialog.</para>
        <sect2 xml:id="general-settings" xreflabel="General Settings">
            <title>General Settings</title>
            <para>Select <menuchoice>
                    <guimenu>File</guimenu>
                    <guimenuitem>Preferences</guimenuitem>
                    <guibutton>General</guibutton>
                </menuchoice> to display the <guilabel>General</guilabel> preferences.</para>
            <sect3>
                <title>Lists and tables</title>
                <para>The <guilabel>Lists and tables</guilabel> group enables you to select the type
                    and size of font used throughout the user interface. The default font and size
                    is dependant on your operating system defaults.</para>
            </sect3>
            <sect3>
                <title>Dives</title>
                <para>The <guilabel>Dives</guilabel> group enables you to define whether or not you
                    want to use a default file for storing dive logs, options include:</para>
                <variablelist>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term><guilabel>No default file</guilabel></term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Select the <guibutton>No default</guibutton> radio button to
                                disable use of a default log file.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term><guilabel>Local default file</guilabel></term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Select the <guibutton>Local default file</guibutton> radio button
                                to enable use of a default log file. By default &productshort; will
                                define a default path and file name for the default. You may choose
                                to remain with the default suggestion or select a different path and
                                file name.</para>
                            <note>
                                <para>Whether you choose to use the suggest default path and file
                                    name or another, you must click the <guibutton>Use
                                        default</guibutton> button to make use of the specified
                                        <guilabel>Local dive log file</guilabel> path.</para>
                            </note>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term><guilabel>Cloud storage default file</guilabel></term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Select the <guibutton>Cloud storage default file</guibutton> radio
                                button to use &productcloud; as the default location for
                                storage.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                </variablelist>
            </sect3>
            <sect3>
                <title>Default Cylinder</title>
                <para>The <guibutton>Use default cylinder</guibutton> drop list displays a list of
                    known scuba cylinder models. When a default is selected it will be used in the
                        <guibutton>Equipment</guibutton> the &paneldiveinfo; panel.</para>
            </sect3>
            <sect3>
                <title>Animations</title>
                <para>Some actions in showing the dive profile are performed using animations. For
                    instance, the axis values for depth and time change from dive to dive. When
                    viewing a different dive, these changes in axis characteristics do not happen
                    instantaneously, but are animated. The _Speed_ of animations can be controlled
                    by setting this slider with faster animation speed to the left, and a 0 value
                    representing no animation at all.</para>
            </sect3>
            <sect3>
                <title>Video thumbnails</title>
                <para>The <guilabel>Video thumbnails</guilabel> group provides settings for
                    management of thumbnails related to videos that may be associated with dives,
                    including:</para>
                <variablelist>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term><guilabel>Extract video thumbnails</guilabel></term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Select the <guibutton>Extract video thumbnails</guibutton>
                                checkbox to enable use of thumbnails.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term><guilabel>ffmpeg executable</guilabel></term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Specify the path to the <application><link
                                        xlink:href="https://www.ffmpeg.org/"
                                    >FFMPEG</link></application> program used to perform
                                manipulation on video files.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term><guilabel>Extract folder</guilabel></term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Slide the <guibutton>Extract folder</guibutton> slider to select
                                the frame within the video timeline to be used as the video
                                thumbnail. The left and right-most positions of the slider position
                                signify the beginning and the end of the video, respectively.</para>
                            <note>
                                <para>If &productshort; cannot determine the length of the video
                                    (this can be the case for AVI files), the first frame of the
                                    video will be used.</para>
                            </note>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                </variablelist>
                <para>For more information please refer to <link
                        xlink:href="appendix-setup-and-configuration#setup-support-for-video-thumbnails"
                        xlink:role="http://docbook.org/xlink/role/olink"/>.</para>
            </sect3>
            <sect3>
                <title>Clear settings</title>
                <para>The <guilabel>Clear settings</guilabel> group enables you to <guibutton>Reset
                        remembered dive computers</guibutton> or <guibutton>Reset all settings back
                        to their default</guibutton>.</para>
            </sect3>
        </sect2>
        <sect2 xml:id="units-settings" xreflabel="Unit Settings">
            <title>Units Settings</title>
            <para>Select <menuchoice>
                    <guimenu>File</guimenu>
                    <guimenuitem>Preferences</guimenuitem>
                    <guibutton>Units</guibutton>
                </menuchoice> to display the <guilabel>Units</guilabel> preferences.</para>
            <sect3>
                <title>Unit system</title>
                <para>Unit of measure options available for the physics properties of a dive,
                        <guilabel>Depth</guilabel>, <guilabel>Pressure</guilabel>,
                        <guilabel>Volume</guilabel>, <guilabel>Temperature</guilabel> and
                        <guilabel>Weight</guilabel>, may be displayed as <guilabel>Metric</guilabel>
                    or <guilabel>Imperial</guilabel>. It is also possible to
                        <guilabel>Personalise</guilabel> which unit of measure system a physics
                    property is measured by.</para>
                <variablelist>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term><guilabel>Metric</guilabel></term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Select the <guibutton>Metric</guibutton> radio button to cause all
                                measures to be displayed using Metric Units of measure.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term><guilabel>Imperial</guilabel></term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Select the <guibutton>Imperial</guibutton> radio button to cause
                                all measures to be displayed using Imperial Units of measure.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term><guilabel>Personalise</guilabel></term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Select the <guibutton>Personalise</guibutton> radio button enable
                                the <guilabel>Individual settings</guilabel> option group.</para>
                            <para>Select either <guibutton>Metric</guibutton> or
                                    <guibutton>Imperial</guibutton> radio buttons for each of the
                                physics properties.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                </variablelist>

            </sect3>
            <sect3>
                <title>Time units</title>
                <para>Time units for the Ascent and Decent portions of dives can be displayed either
                    as <guilabel>Minutes</guilabel> or <guilabel>Seconds</guilabel>.</para>
                <variablelist>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term><guilabel>Minutes</guilabel></term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Select the <guibutton>Minutes</guibutton> radio button to cause
                                Ascent and Decent time units to be displayed as minutes.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term><guilabel>Seconds</guilabel></term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Select the <guibutton>Seconds</guibutton> radio button to cause
                                Ascent and Decent time units to be displayed as seconds.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                </variablelist>
            </sect3>
            <sect3>
                <title>Duration units</title>
                <para>The duration of a dive can be displayed using one of the following
                    options:</para>
                <variablelist>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term><guilabel>hh:mm (always)</guilabel></term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Select the <guibutton>hh:mm (always)</guibutton> radio button to
                                always display dives in the hh:mm format regardless of the
                                duration.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term><guilabel>mm (always)</guilabel></term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Select the <guibutton>mm (always)</guibutton> radio button to
                                always display dives in the mm format regardless of the
                                duration.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term><guilabel>mm (for dives shorter than 1 hour), hh:mm
                                (otherwise)</guilabel></term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Select the <guibutton>mm (for dives shorter than 1 hour), hh:mm
                                    (otherwise)</guibutton> radio button to display dives that are
                                less than 1 hour in mm format and all dives equal to or greater than
                                one hour in length in the hh:mm format.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                </variablelist>
            </sect3>
            <sect3>
                <title>Dive list table</title>
                <para>By default, to conserve screen real-estate and make for easier reading,
                    &productshort; does not display measurement units in the &paneldivelist; panel.
                    This can be changed from the <guilabel>Dive list table</guilabel> option group
                    by checking the <guibutton>Show units in the dive table</guibutton>.</para>
            </sect3>
            <sect3>
                <title>GPS Coordinates</title>
                <para>The <guilabel>GPS Coordinates</guilabel> options group enables you to choose between <guilabel>deg/min/sec</guilabel> and <guilabel>decimal</guilabel> geo-location formats.</para>
            </sect3>
        </sect2>
